---
// WhoFor — qualifies the audience in one breath, with warmth.
---

<section class="section-y bg-surface/60 border-line border-y">
  <div class="container-page grid gap-x-12 gap-y-8 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,1.6fr)]">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-[clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,2.25rem)] leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.01em] text-balance max-w-[14ch]">
      For shops that want to be online — not in the website business.
    </h2>

    <div class="max-w-[52ch] space-y-5 text-[1.0625rem] leading-[1.65] text-ink-soft text-pretty">
      <p>
        You probably know your inventory better than you know HTML, and you'd
        like to keep it that way. Mainstay handles the website end-to-end:
        design, copy guidance, launch, hosting, security, the small monthly
        updates. You stay focused on the shop.
      </p>
      <p>
        I work with one shop at a time so the site feels like the shop, not
        a template. If you're a florist, a bookstore, a record shop, a coffee
        roaster, a hardware store — anything where a real human runs the
        place — we'll get along.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
